# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  Operon Intelligence — Environment Variables Reference
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  DO NOT copy this file directly. Use the per-service templates:
#
#    cp frontend/.env.example  frontend/.env    ← frontend API keys
#    cp backend/.env.example   backend/.env     ← backend API keys
#
#  Or just run:  make env
#
# ─── FRONTEND  (frontend/.env) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  VITE_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY
#    Used by:  frontend/src/services/deepseek.ts
#    Proxied:  Vite dev server proxies /api/deepseek → api.deepseek.com
#    Purpose:  Generates 50 new synthetic complaints every 10 minutes.
#              Without this, the 600-complaint seed pool is static.
#    Optional: Yes — all CFPB data views work without it.
#    Provider: https://platform.deepseek.com
#
#  VITE_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
#
# ─── BACKEND  (backend/.env) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  DEEPSEEK_API_KEY
#    Used by:  backend/agents/orchestrator.py (and all agent files)
#    Endpoint: https://api.deepseek.com/v1/chat/completions
#    Model:    deepseek-chat
#    Purpose:  Powers the 5-agent pipeline:
#              Classification → Compliance Risk → Routing → Resolution → QA
#    Optional: Yes — Agent views (Analyze, Complaints, Audit) will return
#              HTTP 500 without it. Dashboard, LiveFeed, Analysis all work.
#    Provider: https://platform.deepseek.com
#
#  DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
